gw.plugin.policy

Interface IPolicyPlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin, java.rmi.Remote

    public interface IPolicyPlugin
extends com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin
    Plugin that allows customers to customize when particular jobs can start.

      • canStartRewriteNewAccount

        java.lang.String canStartRewriteNewAccount(PolicyPeriod policyPeriod,
                                           java.util.Date effDate,
                                           java.util.Date expDate,
                                           Account account)
        Returns whether or not this PolicyPeriod can be rewritten to a new account.
        Parameters:
        policyPeriod - The policy period to rewrite to a new account. It cannot be null. If the rewrite is started against an expired policy, then this must be the most recent PolicyPeriod in force. Otherwise if the rewrite is started against a canceled policy, this must be the PolicyPeriod in force as of "effDate".
        effDate - The desired effective date of the rewritten period. This must not be null, and it must be on or after the PeriodStart date of "policyPeriod".
        expDate - The desired expiration date of the rewritten period. This must not be null.
        account - The new account to which the policy will be rewritten. This must not be null.
        Returns:
        Null if the job can be started and a non-null error message if it cannot.
